alerts.title: Flood Warning
alerts.description:
...A FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1100 AM CDT FRIDAY FOR
CALHOUN...LINCOLN...MONTGOMERY...WARREN AND NORTHERN GASCONADE
COUNTIES...
Rain has come to an end across the warned area. Heavy rainfall over
the past week, including the 1 to 3 inches of rain that fell in the
past 24 hours, has resulted in the flooding of many low lying areas.
Some highways that are closed due to the flooding include...
Routes BB, K, and J in western Gasconade County
Highway 100 in northern Gasconade County, including in Hermann
Highway 94 in southern Montgomery County and western Warren County
Routes J, K and Y in Montgomery County
Route E in northeast Montgomery County
Routes H and BB in central Lincoln County
Route P in eastern Lincoln County
Many other roads remain impassible due to high water.

alerts.title: Flood Warning
alerts.description:
...A FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 900 AM CDT FRIDAY FOR
MONROE...NORTHERN RANDOLPH...ST. CLAIR AND SOUTH CENTRAL CALHOUN
COUNTIES IN SOUTHWESTERN ILLINOIS...CLINTON AND WASHINGTON COUNTIES
IN SOUTH CENTRAL ILLINOIS...MADISON COUNTY IN SOUTHWESTERN
ILLINOIS...MARION COUNTY IN SOUTH CENTRAL ILLINOIS...ST. CHARLES AND
JEFFERSON COUNTIES IN EAST CENTRAL MISSOURI...NORTHWESTERN STE.
GENEVIEVE COUNTY IN SOUTHEASTERN MISSOURI...FRANKLIN...ST. LOUIS...
SOUTHWESTERN WARREN AND SOUTHERN GASCONADE COUNTIES IN EAST CENTRAL
MISSOURI AND ST. LOUIS CITY...
Rain has come to an end across the area. However, the heavy rainfall
over the past week, including the 1 to 3 inches of rain that fell in
the past 24 hours, has resulted in the flooding of many low lying
areas. This is especially true near smaller creeks, streams and
rivers. Some highways that are closed due to the flooding include...
Eastbound I-44 from I-270 to Hwy 100 in St. Louis and Franklin
Counties Highway 141 near Valley Park in St. Louis County
Highway 30 east of Highway 141
Meramec Bottom Access to I-55
Route 109 south of I-44
Route FF (southbound) in Jefferson County
Route W in Jefferson County
Routes M, K and US-61/67 in eastern Jefferson County near Imperial
Route AA in eastern Jefferson County
Highway 94 and F in southern St. Charles County
Highway B and C in northern St. Charles County
Highway 94 in northern St. Charles County near West Alton
Many other roads remain impassible due to high water.

alerts.title: Flood Warning
alerts.description:
...The flood warning continues for the Cuivre River in
Missouri...
near Troy
at Old Monroe
.This Flood Warning is a result of 2 to 3 inches of precipitation the
past 48 hours and less than one tenth of an inch forecast in the next
24 hours...
The Flood Warning continues for
the Cuivre River near Troy
* until Saturday afternoon.
* At  8:30 PM Thursday the stage was 25.0 feet.
* Flood stage is 21.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* The river has crested and is forecast to continue falling to below
flood stage tomorrow afternoon.
* Impact:  At 25.0 feet...Moderate flooding begins...significant
agricultural land is inundated.
* Impact:  At 24.8 feet...Near this height...Second Street in Moscow
Mills begins flooding near the Byrd Street intersection.
* Impact:  At 23.5 feet...Near this height, State Highway H near the
West Fork Cuivre River bridge will be closed due to flooding.
* Impact:  At 23.2 feet...Gravens Road begins flooding north of
Highway C.
* Impact:  At 23.1 feet...Water begins covering Frenchman Bluff Road
(County Road 658) just west of the Cuivre River bridge.
* Impact:  At 23.0 feet...Considerable agricultural land is flooded
between Troy and Moscow Mills.
* Impact:  At 22.0 feet...Right bank overflows.
* Impact:  At 21.0 feet...Flood Stage.  Left bank overflows.  Minor
flooding begins.
* Impact:  At 18.0 feet...From Highway 61 east to Frenchmans Bluff...
low lying agricultural land is inundated.

...The flood warning continues for the Cuivre River in

near Troy
at Old Monroe
.This Flood Warning is a result of 2 to 3 inches of precipitation the
past 48 hours and less than one tenth of an inch forecast in the next
24 hours...
The Flood Warning continues for
the Cuivre River at Old Monroe
* until Saturday May 13.
* At  7:45 PM Thursday the stage was 28.7 feet.
* Flood stage is 24.0 feet.
* Moderate flooding is forecast.
* The river is forecast to crest near 29.2 feet tomorrow evening,
then slowly fall to below flood stage next Thursday early afternoon.
* Impact:  At 29.1 feet...Streets in Old Monroe begin flooding.
* Impact:  At 28.1 feet...Dyer Road upstream from the gage begins
flooding just downstream of the new Highway 79 bridge.
* Impact:  At 27.0 feet...Right bank overflows.
* Impact:  At 24.5 feet...Extensive left bank agricultural flooding
develops upstream of the gage.  A utility road is flooded along the
Old Monroe levee along the left bank upstream of the gage.
* Impact:  At 24.0 feet...Initial flooding upstream.
* Impact:  At 23.5 feet...Minor agricultural land begins to flood.
